It is important that your engine and fluids are in good shape before you store your vehicle for a long period. Otherwise, you risk having your car not start when you are ready to use it again. Change or top off fluids which may contain sediments as appropriate. This includes oil (Synthetic oil breaks down more slowly with time which makes it preferred for storage), coolant, transmission, and brake fluid. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f7/Prepare-Your-Car-for-Long-Term-Storage-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Prepare-Your-Car-for-Long-Term-Storage-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/f/f7/Prepare-Your-Car-for-Long-Term-Storage-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/aid1378743-v4-728px-Prepare-Your-Car-for-Long-Term-Storage-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Run out windshield washer fluid in regions susceptible to freezing to protect spray hoses from freeze and thaw cracks. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/95/Prepare-Your-Car-for-Long-Term-Storage-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Prepare-Your-Car-for-Long-Term-Storage-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/9/95/Prepare-Your-Car-for-Long-Term-Storage-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/aid1378743-v4-728px-Prepare-Your-Car-for-Long-Term-Storage-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Fill your car with gasoline as it leaves less airspace for moist air to enter the engine and form condensation (or ice) and add a fuel stabilizer available at any hardware/parts store. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a5/Prepare-Your-Car-for-Long-Term-Storage-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Prepare-Your-Car-for-Long-Term-Storage-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/a/a5/Prepare-Your-Car-for-Long-Term-Storage-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/aid1378743-v4-728px-Prepare-Your-Car-for-Long-Term-Storage-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Check belts, filters, hoses, and other components of your engine. Ensure that all are in working order and clean. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7e/Prepare-Your-Car-for-Long-Term-Storage-Step-2Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Prepare-Your-Car-for-Long-Term-Storage-Step-2Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/7/7e/Prepare-Your-Car-for-Long-Term-Storage-Step-2Bullet4.jpg/aid1378743-v4-728px-Prepare-Your-Car-for-Long-Term-Storage-Step-2Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
